    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“we attempt first to describe the ideas and methods currently available for estimating population pharmacokinetic parameters. Next, we contrast these methods by examining their parameter esitmates for the Michaelis-Menten model and a set of data concerning the drug phenytoin. Last, having found differences in the parameters estimated by the various methods, we attempt to elucidate the source of these differences by analysing simulated data so that estimates can be compared to “true” values.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: Included: WT on Vm",
    "observations": "Variability in PK parameters was overestimated using the two-stage approach when compared to the NONMEM estimations. Other parameter values were largely in line with more simplified estimation algorithms.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified PK",
    "equations": "Vm=theta1*WT*exp(eta1) Km=theta2*exp(eta2) DD=((Vm*Css)/(F*(Km+Css)))+eps1 DD is daily dose in mg/kg",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=7.22 theta2=4.44 omega1=0.0551 omega2=0.257 sigma1=0.250",
